Timothy Allan (0233932)
Lab 2 write up

Step by step process of creating a shader:
1.  Set up GLUT and GLEW
2.  Display function to clear the screen and render
3.  Create the shader using this line: GLuint vshader = glCreateShader(GL_VERTEX_SHADER);
4.  Get the location of the shader file
5.  Compile the shader
6.  Check to make sure the shader compiled correctly
7.  Create a program object, using the function glCreateProgram()
8.  Attach the shaders to the program object
9.  Bind the location of each shader to the program object
10. Link your program
11. Check to make sure the program linked correctly
12. Install the program object
13. Set up pointers and stuff
14. Enable the vertex arrays to draw
